
  - *sort-fields* sorts region. The universial argument specifies which
    field should be sorted. (sort-fields 1 BEG END) is equal to
    sort-lines.

    Universal Argument specifies the ARGth field. A negative argument
    starts from the right to count.

  - *sort-regexp-fields* sorts region in a more sophisticated manner.

  <example>
    ;; sort field two
    c 123 bleh
    b 456 blha
    a 789 blah
  </example>

  <example>
    (sort-regexp-fields nil "^. \\([0-9]+\\) .+$" "\\1" 
      (region-beginning) (region-end))
    (sort-regexp-fields nil "^.*$" "[0-9]+" 
      (region-beginning) (region-end))
    (sort-numeric-fields 2 
      (region-beginning) (region-end))
  </example>

  - *sort-numeric-fields*

  <example>
     ;; sort field one
     16     travel
    189     tools
  </example>

  <example>
    (sort-numeric-fields 2 
      (region-beginning) (region-end))
  </example>
